     1	import spacy
     2	
     3	def spacy_result_to_conll(sentence):
     4	    """
     5	    Generates a dependency parse for the input sentence in the CoNLL-U format.
     6	
     7	    Args:
     8	        sentence (`str`): An input sentence.
     9	    
    10	    Retruns:
    11	        conll_output (`str`): A dependency parse for the input sentence in the CoNLL-U format.
    12	    """
    13	
    14	
    15	
    16	nlp = spacy.load("en_core_web_sm")
    17	    doc = nlp(sentence)
    18	
    19	    header = ["ID", "text", "LEMMA", "POS", "Tag", "FEATS", "HEAD", "DEPREL", "DEPS", "MISC"]
    20	    conll_output = "{:<5} {:<10} {:<10} {:<6} {:<6} {:<6} {:<6} {:<8} {:<6} {:<6}\n".format(*header)
    21	
    22	    for token in doc:
    23	        row = [
    24	            token.i + 1,  # ID
    25	            token.text,   # FORM
    26	            token.lemma_, # LEMMA
    27	            token.pos_,   # UPOS
    28	            token.tag_,   # XPOS
    29	            "_",          # FEATS
    30	            token.head.i + 1, # HEAD
    31	            token.dep_,   # DEPREL
    32	            "_",          # DEPS
    33	            "_"           # MISC
    34	        ]
    35	        conll_output += "{:<5} {:<10} {:<10} {:<6} {:<6} {:<6} {:<6} {:<8} {:<6} {:<6}\n".format(*row)
    36	
    37	    return conll_output
